# KyleBernelle.github.io

\# \*\*Rivals of Aether 2\*\*  	\*\*Steam Workshop Guide\*\* 



\## \*\*Purpose:\*\* 



This document serves as a run-down/tutorial of the process of creating a new character and operating the mod kit. 



\## \*\*Architecture:\*\* 



\*\*!\[]\[image1]\*\*



\# \*\*Lua API Documentation\*\* 



To access the lua API documentation:



\* Navigate to the Resources folder and open the “\*\*Lua API Documentation\*\*” shortcut  

&nbsp; \* This will open a doxygen page with all of the classes and functions currently exposed to Lua 



&nbsp;   # \*\*Installing the Mod Kit\*\* 



\* Ensure you have access to the Rivals\\\_Modkit repository  

\* You will find 4 folders: download these and extract them all to the same location on your PC



&nbsp; !\[]\[image2]



&nbsp;  \*Your final folder should look like the image above\*





&nbsp; 





&nbsp; \*\*Editor\*\* \\- Contains a pre-built version of the editor based on the RoA2 Editor 



&nbsp; \*\*Example Mods\*\* \\- Will contain an example of mods developed by the team, this is where we can include Armando for reference for modders.



&nbsp; \*\*Project\*\* \\- This is the Rivals of Aether 2 game project, it currently contains all the assets you would normally find in the game, but no source code 



&nbsp; \*\*Resources\*\* \\- Documents similar to this will exist here in the future to ship with the mod kit to provide offline documentation for modders. 



&nbsp; ### \*\*Open the Editor\*\* 



1\. Make sure you have Steam running on your PC  

&nbsp;  \* \*\*You must own a copy of Rivals of Aether 2\*\*   

2\. Click on the OpenProject.bat in the Project folder   

&nbsp;  \* …\\\\Rivals2\\\_Modkit\\\\Project\\\\OpenProject.bat



&nbsp;    ### \*\*The Modding Window\*\* 



&nbsp;    To access the modding window:   

\* Click “\*\*Modding\*\*” in the toolbar at the top of the Unreal Editor window  

\* Click “\*\*Open Steam Workshop UI\*\*”



&nbsp; The following window will appear: 



&nbsp; !\[]\[image3]





&nbsp; \*\*Legend:\*\* 



&nbsp; \*\*1\*\* \\- The title of your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*2\*\* \\- A description of your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*3\*\* \\- Developer Tags for your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*4\*\* \\- Path to the root of your mod content 



&nbsp; \*\*5\*\* \\- Path to a preview image for your mod



&nbsp; \*\*6\*\* \\- Mod Visibility to users 



&nbsp; \*\*7\*\* \\- Language of your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*8\*\* \\- A description of changes made to your mod for this update 



&nbsp; \*\*9\*\* \\- An area to display error messages related to uploading your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*10\*\* \\- The current update handle for your mod (should not be blank) 



&nbsp; \*\*11\*\* \\- A preview area of the info for your mod (image, title, description) 



&nbsp; \*\*12\*\* \\- A read out of all the files to be packaged with your mod 



&nbsp; \*\*13\*\* \\- A button to create a new mod (will instantly make it on the Steam Workshop with empty info) 



&nbsp; \*\*14\*\* \\- Load your pre-existing mod information 



&nbsp; \*\*15\*\* \\- Close the current mod you are working on, saves the mod info and allows you to create a new mod 



&nbsp; \*\*16\*\* \\- Publish your mod information to your mod on the Steam Workshop
